The paper focuses on visual grounding, which involves combining language and vision to understand the relationship between objects in an image. This falls under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses biases in datasets and the need for better understanding of machine learning methods, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
